            "image_alt": "The Kaunas garage - two borrowed screens",
            "kicker": "// HOW IT STARTED",
            "heading": "It started in a garage with a borrowed rig.",
            "body": "<p>No business plan, no investors, no warehouse. Just two screens, a kettle that's seen things, and a stubborn idea: make clothes that argue with you a little, and make them so well you can't ignore them.</p>"
          }
        },
        "row_2": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "side": "right",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/hero-2-alt.png",
            "image_alt": "Lena at the light table - designing a chapter",
            "kicker": "// HOW WE WORK",
            "heading": "We write the story before we cut the cloth.",
            "body": "<p>Every chapter is built around a character and a world, not a season. We design the pieces to live inside that story, make exactly 8, drop them once, and move on. It's slower, harder, and far more fun than chasing a trend calendar.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "row_1",
        "row_2"
      ],
